subSubSection.paragraph:
Nematothecae short, tubular, with a small peduncle and somewhat everted rim with a few renovations; a subtle sub-marginal narrowing is sometimes present. Base flat, with rounded corners. Abundance variable, being numerous proximally in the stem of some colonies and scarce in others; 
1–2
(rarely) occur typically on the hydrothecal apophyses. Others appear scattered on hydrocaulus and branches arising from secondary tubes, being normally absent on monosiphonic hydrocauli.
